Objective¶

Fatal drug overdoses account for a significant portion of accidental deaths in adolescents and young adults. It is currently the leading cause of death in the United States.

The objective of the research is to examine trends in misuse drugs with drug-related overdose deaths in Connecticut. We are going to analyze the values we find in the data and understand the pattern. Such as the most common drugs that cause death, age range and so on. This analysis will be useful for policymakers when it comes to drug control strategies.

The Dataset and Data Loading¶

The dataset is a listing of each accidental death associated with drug overdose in Connecticut from 2012 to 2018. Deaths are by grouped age, race, ethnicity, and gender and by the types of drugs detected post-death.

In [286]:
#load the datafuke
filename = '/Users/ashleahuang/Desktop/drug1.json'
with open (filename) as f:
    file = json.load(f)
#checking the type
type(file)
Out[286]:
list

Findings¶

Based on data, it definately indicates the non-medical use of opioid prescription medication and other drug abuse. You can see that other recreational drugs are on the top of the list too. Cocaine is no.4 while ehanol - alcohol is on no.6.

However, the top 3 are heorin, anyopioid and fentanyl. These are all opioid related, in the meantime, heroin is the highest of all. It seems like the consequence of opioid abuse if the door to haeorin addiction when the supply of opioids cannot be abtained.

The majority of the overdose deaths are currently among caucasian, around 80%; men, 75%; and mainly people in age group 25-40. In addition, opioid related drugs are involved in almost most of all overdose deaths in this dataset, such as heroin, tramad, morphone, amphet, fentanyl and so on.

From what we have found, it seems like Connecticut experienced large amount of opiod-involved overdose deaths and it is highly driven by fentanyl and polysubstance use.

Policymakers need to consider that people who misuse drugs may have somewhat different motivations, and need different treatments and prevention efforts.

Recommendations¶

Nowadays, misuse and addiction to drugs including prescription pain relievers, heroin, opioids related and recreational drugs is a national crisis which is affecting the serious public health.

While many initiatives are working to reduce opioid prescription misuse, and try to understand the potential consequences of polysubstance use in accidental overdose deaths. I believe it is also important to enhence the drug control and drug education.

The reason why I find it neccessary to enhance drug control and drug education is because we are also dealing with misuse of drugs and potential of recreational drug use. Therefore, we need to look at the availability of the drugs.

There are two ways to find opioids or any other drugs: it is either legally through an MD or illegally through a drug dealer. In order to obtain drugs users and dealers are taking advantage of social media and personal contact tools such as snapchat and telegram for transaction.

There is no easy way to fix the situation and there has to be more creative ways of developing effective drug education. In order to make this work, both goverment and citizens need to put in the effort to estabalish effective strategies for preventaion and early intervation for opioid addtion.
